Submit Your Event
We look forward to partnering with you on your event in Gulf County.  To help market your event, we ask that you fill in the form below and attach the required files 45 days before the event.  Your event must be open to the public, be tourist geared, align with the Gulf County brand, and enhance the visitor experience. As the central marketing team for Gulf County, Florida, the GCTDC is committed to working together to implement broad-based messaging, awareness, and communications to attract visitors to Gulf County during and for the events.
If you are marketing your event on social media, we would like to ask you to add us as a co-sponsor so we can elevate the reach of your event.
If you have questions, please feel free to
email Summer.

Events
Celebrate Beach Town Style
We have a lot to celebrate in Gulf County, all in a laid-back atmosphere without the crowds. Come celebrate beach town style with us.
No matter what time of year you find yourself in Gulf County, there’s always something exciting to do.  We keep our
event calenda
r jam-packed with live music, kid-friendly fun, festivals and more.
Plan your trip around an event that appeals to you.  From food to culture, art and music, Gulf County offers something that appeals to everyone.
Gulf County has many events throughout the year so check back regularly to keep up-to-date on all of them.  Plus a few of signature events take place each year at the same time so you can go ahead book your

Kayak & Paddle Boarding
Either Oar -The Choice is Yours.
Grab your kayak or paddleboard and catch the drift on one of our diverse waterways.  Launch your kayak and glide for miles above the pristine, shallow bottom of
St. Joseph Bay
. With clear water, you can easily spot dolphins, sea turtles and an array of fish; so be sure to pack your binoculars AND fishing rod. For the seasoned paddler, the 2.5-mile paddle from St. Joe Beach to the remote tip of Cape San Blas is an exhilarating trip.
Want a change of scenery where you’re likely to find eagles, alligators and an experience with nature you’ll never forget? Head to North Gulf County to kayak the mysterious
Dead Lakes
in Wewahitchka.
What’s SUP? Enjoy a bird’s eye view above one of our calm waters and soak in the beauty of Gulf County. Local outfitters can get you on the water with a kayak or paddleboard for the day or the week. If you’re looking for expert knowledge, hook up with a local guide. No matter what you choose, there is plenty of space (and water) for everyone!
Watch this video
of a bird’s eye view of the natural wonder of the Dead Lakes.  You can launch your own kayak and tour or contact a local charter today.

Your Winter Adventure Awaits
Welcome to Gulf County, where we believe winter is best enjoyed Sunny Side Up!
This winter, trade the frost for sunshine and experience Gulf County, Florida, like never before. Whether you’re a snowbird, a family looking for new memories, or a couple seeking a peaceful retreat, Gulf County is your perfect winter escape. With average temperatures in the mid-60s to low 70s, it's the ideal time to enjoy our sun-drenched shores, outdoor adventures, and vibrant community events.
Join Us for Sun-Soaked Fun and Endless Adventure
From November to March, Gulf County comes alive with an array of exciting winter events designed to bring people together. Whether it’s beach bonfires, guided nature tours, or local artisan markets, you’ll find that the community here is as warm as the weather. This season, we’re celebrating life on the sunny side—where every day offers something new to discover and cherish.
Plan Your Winter Getaway
Our concierges are ready to help you create the perfect, stress-free winter vacation. Whether you're a first-time visitor or one of our cherished return guests, we’re here to make sure your stay is seamless. Stop by our Welcome Center to reconnect and get personalized recommendations on the best local activities, hidden gems, and community events. For returning guests, your arrival is our celebration—come back and experience more of the Gulf County charm you love!
Weekly Happenings
There are a lot of cool things happening in Gulf County every week. Here are just a few. Check out their websites for all the details on these events and more.
Haughty Heron:
live entertainment Friday and Saturday evenings
St. Joe Bar & Package:
pool tournaments every Wednesday, NFL Sunday Ticket
Scallop RePUBlic:
Live music 7-10 Thursday-Saturday
Lookout Lounge:
Weekly events including pool tournament, dart tournament, karaoke, live music, and more!
Bingo at the VFW
: Bingo every Monday starting at 5:30, and Trivia every second Thursday of the Month
Bridge at FUMC:
Mondays 1 pm in the Great Hall at First United Methodist Church. Call Diana to reserve a seat to play. 810-338-4830

The Gulf County Tourist Development Council Advisory Board
would like to thank you for visiting our website and, hopefully, our quiet shores along the Gulf of America. We are here to help answer any questions you may have about our unspoiled natural environment and our welcoming communities. Our goal is to help visitors and locals alike enjoy all that Gulf County offers and create lasting memories in this special place we call home.
The Gulf County Tourist Development Council (TDC)
is dedicated to supporting tourism that enhances both visitor experiences and the quality of life for our residents. The TDC is funded through tourism bed-tax collected in Gulf County, and these funds are reinvested to promote our destination, protect our natural assets, and encourage sustainable growth.
The Advisory Board is comprised of members appointed by the Gulf County Board of County Commissioners. The board includes representatives from tourism-related businesses, local accommodations, community leaders, and elected officials. Together, they provide guidance on tourism initiatives and ensure that Gulf County remains a welcoming destination for all.

Annual Tourist Development Tax Collections (TDT)
The Tourist Development Tax (commonly referred to as the "bed tax") funds the marketing and promotional activities performed by the Gulf County Tourist Development Council. The tax is also used for beach cleaning and grooming, product improvement, and beach nourishment. To find out more information on the Tourist Development Tax, contact the Clerk of Court's office at
850-229-6112
